%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22Hate%20office%20politics%3F%20It%20all%20comes%20down%20to%20point%20of%20view.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22640%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Deb%20Liu%20Facebook%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F523203bfeab8ea4d5a966704%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EFacebook%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fdebliu.substack.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EPerspectives%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0is%20a%20weekly%20newsletter%20about%20careers%2C%20leadership%2C%20and%20growth%20by%20Ancestry%20CEO%20Deb%20Liu.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ELiu%20writes%20that%20it's%20important%20to%20get%20a%20sense%20of%20why%20the%20people%20you%20work%20with%20act%20the%20way%20they%20do.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EShe%20also%20offers%20strategies%20like%20demonstrate%20openness%20to%20deal%20with%20someone%20who%20seems%20political.%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20hate%20office%20politics.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20something%20someone%20said%20to%20me%20at%20a%20Women%20in%20Product%20event%20in%20Seattle.%20I%20replied%2C%20%26quot%3BOffice%20politics%20is%20like%20the%20weather.%20Ignore%20it%20at%20your%20own%20peril.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnyone%20who%20works%20in%20the%20corporate%20world%20can%20tell%20you%20that%20the%20word%20%26quot%3Boffice%26quot%3B%20coupled%20with%20the%20word%20%26quot%3Bpolitics%26quot%3B%20is%20a%20hated%20combination.%20Over%20the%20years%2C%20however%2C%20I've%20noticed%20something.%20Everyone%20who%20works%20for%20a%20company%20feels%20like%20there's%20a%20lot%20of%20politics%2C%20but%20ask%20them%20and%20they%20will%20tell%20you%20with%20complete%20confidence%20that%20they%20themselves%20are%20not%20political.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThink%20about%20that%20for%20a%20second.%20How%20can%20this%20apparent%20contradiction%20be%20true%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20all%20comes%20down%20to%20point%20of%20view.%20From%20our%20perspective%2C%20everyone%20else%20seems%20to%20be%20playing%20politics%20because%20that's%20our%20interpretation%20of%20their%20behavior.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdebliu.substack.com%2Fp%2Ftough-love-how-hard-feedback-changed%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EBut%20our%20lenses%20for%20viewing%20our%20own%20behavior%20are%20colored%20by%20our%20intent.%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cem%3EWe%3C%2Fem%3E%20do%20things%20for%20%3Cem%3Ereasons%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Ebut%20%3Cem%3Eothers%3C%2Fem%3E%20do%20things%20because%20they%20are%20%3Cem%3Epolitical.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20if%20we%20could%20see%20office%20politics%20from%20a%20totally%20different%20perspective%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EUnderstanding%20office%20politics%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20recent%20survey%20of%20800%20people%20published%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.latimes.com%2Fbusiness%2Fstory%2F2023-05-01%2Foffice-politics-just-as-toxic-work-from-home-era%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ELos%20Angeles%20Times%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3E40%25%20of%20participants%20reported%20they%20had%20considered%20leaving%20a%20job%20because%20of%20office%20politics%2C%20and%2025%25%20reported%20they%20had%20actually%20left%20their%20job%20over%20it.%3C%2Fa%3E%20But%20what%20if%20the%20problem%20isn't%20%26quot%3Bpolitics%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20how%20we%20interpret%20it%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EContrary%20to%20how%20they%20may%20seem%2C%20most%20of%20the%20people%20you%20work%20with%20are%20not%20terrible%20people.%20They%20are%20not%20out%20to%20get%20you.%20Their%20goal%20is%20not%20to%20make%20your%20life%20harder.%20They%20struggle%20with%20the%20same%20things%20you%20do%2C%20from%20a%20lack%20of%20clarity%20to%20overwhelming%20pressure.%20All%20the%20negative%20things%20we%20go%20through%20in%20our%20jobs%20are%20likely%20things%20our%20coworkers%20have%20had%20to%20deal%20with%20too%20%E2%80%94%20but%20none%20of%20us%20see%20it%20that%20way.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20isn't%20to%20say%20there%20aren't%20people%20out%20there%20who%20are%20genuinely%20disruptive%2C%20terrible%20to%20work%20with%2C%20or%20who%20try%20to%20steal%20credit.%20But%20for%20the%20most%20part%2C%20people's%20behaviors%20are%20a%20response%20to%20the%20incentives%20they're%20given%2C%20whether%20positive%20or%20negative.%20At%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20we%20are%20all%20organisms%20that%20can%20only%20do%20our%20best%20to%20adapt%20to%20whatever%20context%20we%20find%20ourselves%20in.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20remember%20a%20sermon%20at%20church%20where%20the%20pastor%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BAnger%20is%20a%20will%20thwarted.%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BPolitics%2C%26quot%3B%20likewise%2C%20is%20someone%20else%20acting%20according%20to%20their%20will%2C%20even%20if%20that%20goes%20against%20someone%20else's.%20Many%20times%2C%20when%20we%20talk%20about%20politics%2C%20we%20are%20talking%20about%20being%20on%20the%20other%20side%20of%20someone%20with%20deeply%20different%20goals%20than%20us.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThink%20about%20the%20following%20scenarios%3A%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20are%20told%20by%20your%20manager%20that%20in%20order%20to%20get%20that%20promotion%2C%20you%20need%20to%20ship%20a%20feature%20before%20the%20end%20of%20the%20quarter.%20Someone%20comes%20to%20you%20from%20across%20the%20company%20who%20desperately%20needs%20resources%20for%20a%20critical%20project.%20Do%20you%20stop%20what%20you%20are%20doing%20to%20help%2C%20knowing%20you%20will%20miss%20your%20deadline%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20are%20told%20that%20there%20are%20limited%20engineering%20resources%20and%20that%20you%20have%20to%20make%20your%20best%20case%20to%20get%20your%20initiative%20funded.%20Then%20you%20realize%20something%20else%20should%20be%20a%20higher%20priority%20for%20the%20company.%20Do%20you%20tell%20the%20VP%20to%20put%20the%20resources%20there%20instead%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20are%20told%20there%20is%20one%20opening%20to%20become%20the%20team%20manager%2C%20and%20you%20are%20up%20for%20it.%20Do%20you%20yield%20to%20your%20peer%2C%20who%20is%20equally%20good%20and%20has%20more%20experience%20than%20you%2C%20or%20do%20you%20fight%20for%20the%20position%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20scenarios%20like%20these%2C%20our%20own%20incentives%2C%20the%20incentives%20of%20the%20company%2C%20and%20the%20incentives%20of%20others%20may%20not%20be%20aligned.%20There%20isn't%20a%20%26quot%3Bgood%20guy%26quot%3B%20or%20a%20%26quot%3Bbad%20guy%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20we%20may%20not%20even%20notice%20this.%20We're%20willing%20to%20forgive%20ourselves%20for%20being%20selfish%20in%20order%20to%20get%20that%20promotion%20or%20to%20land%20that%20funding.%20We%20are%20partisan%20and%20fight%20for%20our%20teams%2C%20refusing%20to%20look%20at%20the%20bigger%20picture.%20How%20does%20that%20look%20to%20the%20person%20on%20the%20other%20side%20of%20the%20issue%20%E2%80%94%20the%20coworker%20who%20wants%20that%20role%20just%20as%20badly%2C%20or%20the%20team%20who%20may%20need%20those%20resources%20more%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20where%20they're%20standing%2C%20we%20must%20seem%20awfully%20political.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EPerception%20versus%20reality%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20once%20worked%20with%20someone%20who%20others%20felt%20was%20always%20playing%20politics.%20I%20knew%20their%20reputation%2C%20but%20I%20never%20put%20much%20stock%20in%20it%20because%20I%20knew%20who%20they%20were%20and%20what%20they%20truly%20cared%20about.%20It%20drove%20me%20crazy%20to%20hear%20others%20talk%20about%20someone%20I%20respected%20so%20negatively%2C%20so%20I%20set%20out%20to%20understand%20it.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20it%20turned%20out%2C%20the%20disparity%20was%20that%20he%20was%20an%20information%20gatherer.%20He%20would%20speak%20to%20a%20large%20number%20of%20people%20to%20understand%20the%20general%20sentiment%20and%20get%20support%20for%20his%20ideas.%20Because%20he%20was%20so%20well-connected%20and%20knew%20everything%20that%20was%20happening%20(he%20was%20talking%20to%20a%20lot%20of%20people%2C%20after%20all%2C)%20others%20didn't%20see%20his%20behavior%20as%20genuine.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20was%20interesting%20was%20that%20the%20broadest%20swath%20of%20people%20who%20attributed%20his%20behavior%20to%20politics%20were%20the%20ones%20who%20were%20farther%20removed%20from%20him.%20Those%20who%20worked%20with%20him%20more%20closely%20were%20able%20to%20see%20how%20gathering%20information%20made%20him%20more%20effective.%20It%20was%20like%20night%20and%20day.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20less%20perspective%20you%20have%20on%20someone%2C%20the%20more%20likely%20you%20are%20to%20draw%20incorrect%20conclusions%20about%20them.%20Even%20when%20you're%20close%20to%20them%2C%20only%20they%20can%20truly%20know%20what's%20going%20on%20in%20their%20mind.%20Consider%20that%20the%20people%20who%20seem%20to%20be%20playing%20sides%2C%20backstabbing%2C%20or%20stirring%20up%20drama%20might%20actually%20be%20trying%20to%20act%20in%20the%20best%20interest%20of%20the%20company%20or%20their%20teams.%20For%20all%20you%20know%2C%20they're%20just%20doing%20the%20best%20they%20can%20with%20what%20they%20have%2C%20the%20same%20way%20you%20are.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20will%20be%20times%20when%20you%20see%20others%20acting%20politically%2C%20and%20there%20will%20be%20times%20when%20you%20will%20seem%20political%20to%20others.%20The%20bigger%20question%20is%20how%20you%20will%20respond.%20Do%20you%20extend%20grace%20and%20understanding%2C%20or%20do%20you%20feed%20into%20the%20maligning%20machine%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAligning%20perspectives%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%2C%20when%20I%20was%20running%20a%20platform%20team%2C%20we%20wanted%20to%20implement%20a%20feature%20that%20was%20within%20the%20user%20experience%20of%20another%20team.%20They%20put%20us%20through%20the%20wringer%2C%20fighting%20us%20every%20step%20of%20the%20way.%20The%20product%20was%20objectively%20in%20high%20demand%20by%20our%20customers%2C%20and%20it%20was%20a%20company%20priority%20from%20the%20top.%20But%20they%20made%20every%20single%20meeting%20a%20battle%2C%20picking%20over%20every%20pixel.%20Every%20person%2C%20up%20and%20down%20both%20teams%2C%20felt%20the%20disconnect.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEverything%20changed%20when%20one%20day%20I%20told%20the%20other%20team%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20want%20you%20to%20stop%20thinking%20about%20this%20as%20me%20asking%20you%20to%20put%20%5Bthis%20feature%5D%20in%20your%20experience.%20I%20want%20you%20to%20see%20this%20as%20us%20building%20something%20for%20you%20that%20you%20own%20and%20can%20take%20to%20market%20as%20your%20own.%20You%20should%20name%20it%20anything%20you%20want.%26quot%3B%20Suddenly%20it%20was%20like%20a%20switch%20flipped.%20We%20immediately%20went%20from%20adversaries%20to%20co-creators%2C%20all%20it%20took%20was%20forming%20a%20shared%20perspective.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20often%20see%20other%20people's%20teams%20as%20%26quot%3Bthe%20other.%26quot%3B%20I%20hear%20this%20a%20lot%2C%20and%20I%20myself%20was%20guilty%20of%20this%20earlier%20in%20my%20career.%20I%20felt%20like%20I%20had%20to%20fight%20for%20my%20team%20and%20our%20goals.%20I%20saw%20relationships%20as%20adversarial%2C%20not%20collaborative.%20It%20took%20me%20years%20to%20understand%20that%20when%20you%20create%20us-vs-them%20relationships%2C%20you%20are%2C%20by%20necessity%2C%20creating%20the%20very%20politics%20you%20hate.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20if%20instead%2C%20you%20could%20look%20for%20ways%20to%20connect%20over%20shared%20goals%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EReducing%20politics%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20genuinely%20get%20to%20know%20someone%2C%20you%20have%20a%20better%20sense%20of%20who%20they%20are%20and%20why%20they%20act%20the%20way%20they%20do.%20Often%2C%20gaining%20more%20perspective%20on%20someone%20forces%20us%20to%20reevaluate%20how%20we%20viewed%20their%20actions%20before.%20The%20more%20context%20you%20have%2C%20the%20harder%20it%20is%20to%20write%20their%20behavior%20off%20as%20political.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20once%20worked%20with%20a%20leader%20who%20displayed%20an%20%26quot%3Beither%20you're%20with%20me%20or%20against%20me%26quot%3B%20style.%20It%20made%20everything%20feel%20like%20a%20zero-sum%20game%2C%20and%20I%20found%20it%20off-putting.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20I%20had%20a%20hard%20time%20navigating%20the%20relationship.%20But%20then%2C%20when%20we%20ended%20up%20on%20the%20same%20team%2C%20I%20found%20him%20to%20be%20wonderful%20to%20work%20with.%20It%20was%20hard%20to%20square%20the%20version%20of%20him%20I%20was%20seeing%20then%20with%20the%20picture%20of%20him%20I'd%20had%20before.%20I%20realized%20that%20I%20had%20not%20taken%20the%20time%20to%20get%20to%20know%20him%20before%2C%20and%20I%20hadn't%20really%20understood%20his%20perspective%20because%20we%20sat%20in%20different%20organizations.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESometimes%2C%20all%20it%20takes%20to%20see%20the%20reality%20of%20a%20situation%20is%20a%20little%20more%20context.%20Try%20these%20strategies%20the%20next%20time%20you%20find%20yourself%20dealing%20with%20someone%20who%20seems%20political%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3ETake%20a%20step%20back.%20Recognize%20that%20your%20perception%20of%20them%20may%20be%20coloring%20your%20view.%20Consider%20that%20they%20may%20not%20see%20their%20own%20behaviors%20as%20political.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EAsk%20for%20their%20perspective.%20Listen%20closely%20and%20directly%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that%20means%20not%20just%20waiting%20for%20your%20turn%20to%20speak.%20Actively%20try%20to%20understand%20why%20they%20seem%20hostile%20to%20you%20or%20your%20idea.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EDemonstrate%20openness%20to%20hearing%20their%20point%20of%20view%20without%20prejudice.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EGet%20outside%20input.%20How%20do%20people%20who%20work%20closely%20with%20them%20view%20their%20behavior%3F%20Do%20they%20have%20a%20different%20perception%20than%20those%20who%20are%20farther%20removed%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EPut%20yourself%20in%20their%20shoes.%20Why%20would%20they%20say%20what%20they%20said%3F%20Could%20your%20behavior%20have%20played%20a%20role%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20all%20you%20have%20to%20base%20your%20opinion%20on%20is%20your%20perception%20of%20someone%20else's%20actions%2C%20you%20risk%20jumping%20to%20conclusions%20and%20burning%20bridges.%20Instead%2C%20look%20for%20ways%20to%20expand%20your%20viewpoint%20and%20get%20more%20insight%20into%20the%20logic%20behind%20their%20behavior.%20You%20may%20find%20that%20they%20no%20longer%20appear%20political%20at%20all.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cbr%3E%3Cem%3EDeb%20Liu%20is%20CEO%20of%20Ancestry%20and%20a%20Silicon%20Valley%20tech%20executive%20of%20nearly%20two%20decades.%20Read%20more%20in%20her%20Substack%20newsletter%2C%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fdebliu.substack.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EPerspectives%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhate-office-politics-good-luck-trying-to-steer-clear-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696065661000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651729535640b20019d77f0d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%