)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fftx-spent-millions-chartering-jets-to-dc-amazon-deliveries-2023-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Here's%20how%20much%20you%20should%20tip%20at%20restaurants%2C%20salons%2C%20hotels%20%E2%80%94%26nbsp%3Bfor%20food%20delivery%2C%20and%20more%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22889%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22tipping%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651200ae59fd710019f0145e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMany%20Americans%20feel%20confused%20or%20frustrated%20about%20how%20much%20to%20tip%20these%20days.%20We%20asked%20etiquette%20experts%20for%20their%20advice.%3Cp%3EAnastasiya%20Aleksandrenko%2FShutterstock%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%20%3Cli%3EA%20growing%20number%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcustomers-being-asked-to-tip-everywhere-theyre-sick-of-it-2023-3%5C%22%3Ebusinesses%20are%20requesting%20tips%20from%20customers%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EYet%2C%20the%20rules%20of%20tipping%20depend%20on%20all%20kinds%20of%20different%20factors%2C%20etiquette%20experts%20say.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EHere's%20how%20much%20you%20should%20tip%20for%20restaurants%2C%20delivery%2C%20salons%2C%20Uber%20rides%2C%20and%20more.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20a%20big%20question%20about%20whether%20you%20should%20tip%20a%20server%20in%20a%20sit-down%20restaurant%3A%20That's%20pretty%20well-established.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20what%20about%20all%20the%20other%20places%20where%20tip%20jars%20%E2%80%94%20virtual%20or%20otherwise%20%E2%80%94%20are%20popping%20up%2C%20especially%20since%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbusinesses-ask-for-tips-pay-workers-less-recession-fears-2023-7%5C%22%3Epandemic%20upended%20tipping%20norms%3C%2Fa%3E%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSome%20people%20are%20feeling%20unwanted%20social%20pressure%20to%20tip%20in%20circumstances%20and%20amounts%20that%20they%20don't%20really%20want%20to%2C%20and%20that's%20making%20them%20unhappy%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20tipping%20expert%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.tippingresearch.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMichael%20Lynn%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20is%20a%20professor%20of%20consumer%20behavior%20and%20marketing%20at%20the%20Cornell%20University%20School%20of%20Hotel%20Administration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20there%20are%20some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftipping-restaurant-takeout-coffee-checkout-should-i-tip-etiquette-tips-2023-9%5C%22%3Escenarios%20where%20it's%20perfectly%20okay%20not%20to%20tip%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it's%20clear%20that%20the%20expectations%20of%20tipping%20culture%20are%20a%20bit%20higher%20these%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20anyone%20who's%20a%20little%20lost%20on%20how%20much%20you%20should%20be%20leaving%20at%20places%20like%20restaurants%2C%20bars%2C%20and%20salons%2C%20we%20polled%20experts%20to%20find%20out.%20Here's%20what%20they%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3ESit-down%20restaurants%3A%20Around%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3E20%25%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EThomas%20Farley%2C%20a%20New%20York-based%20etiquette%20expert%20known%20as%20Mister%20Manners%2C%20said%20you%20should%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famericans-cheap-bad-restaurant-tipping-best-worst-states-2023-9%5C%22%3Etip%20at%20least%2020%25%20at%20sit-down%20restaurants%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20us%20as%20patrons%2C%20the%20expectation%20is%20you%20are%20always%20tipping%20those%20employees%20because%20that%20is%20truly%20how%20they%20make%20their%20income%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EWait%20staff%20who%20earn%20the%20bulk%20of%20their%20wages%20through%20tips%20are%20often%20paid%20less%20than%20minimum%20wage%20by%20their%20employer.%20While%20the%20amount%20varies%20across%20the%20states%20that%20allow%20sub-minimum%20wages%2C%20it's%20lower%20than%20the%20actual%20minimum%20wage.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20New%20York%2C%20for%20example%2C%20the%20minimum%20wage%20for%20food%20service%20workers%20falls%20between%20%2414.20%20and%20%2415%20an%20hour.%20But%20depending%20on%20where%20they%20work%20in%20the%20state%20food%20service%20workers%20earn%20between%20%249.45%20and%20%2410%20an%20hour%20in%20cash%20wages%20paid%20by%20their%20employers%20%E2%80%94%20and%20rely%20on%20tips%20to%20make%20up%20the%20difference%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdol.ny.gov%2Fminimum-wage-0%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20New%20York%20State%20Department%20of%20Labor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20amounts%20are%20different%2C%20but%20the%20concept%20is%20the%20same%20in%20many%20other%20states%2C%20too.%20That's%20why%20tips%2C%20according%20to%20Farley%2C%20are%20%26quot%3Bpart%20of%20the%20compact%20you%20enter%20when%20you%20sit%20down%20at%20a%20restaurant%20and%20you%20are%20getting%20service.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20if%20you're%20one%20notch%20higher%2C%20at%20a%20fine-dining%20establishment%2C%20expect%20to%20leave%2020%25%20to%2025%25%2C%20said%20etiquette%20expert%20Avery%20Johnson%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.southernacademyofetiquette.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Southern%20Academy%20of%20Etiquette%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EBars%3A%20%241%20to%20%243%20per%20drink%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ETip%20your%20bartender%2015%20to%2020%25%20of%20your%20tab%2C%20which%20could%20be%20somewhere%20between%20%241%20to%20%243%20per%20drink%2C%20according%20to%20Johnson%2C%20and%20Nick%20Leighton%2C%20an%20etiquette%20expert%20and%20co-host%20of%20the%20podcast%20%26quot%3BWere%20You%20Raised%20By%20Wolves%3F%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EDelivery%3A%20At%20least%2015%25%2C%20but%20consider%20distance%2C%20too%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20DoorDash%20driver%20cursed%20at%20a%20woman%20who%20tipped%20%245%20on%20a%20%2420%20order%2C%20which%20is%2025%25%2C%20Insider%20asked%20food%20delivery%20drivers%20in%20New%20York%20how%20much%20they%20expect%20to%20receive%20in%20tips.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20of%20them%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-much-to-tip-food-delivery-driver-doordash-ubereats-2023-7%5C%22%3Esaid%2015%25%20to%2020%25%20would%20constitute%20a%20good%20tip%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20in%20New%20York%2C%20of%20course%2C%20distances%20are%20nominal%20in%20such%20a%20compact%20city.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20cities%2C%20when%20a%20driver%20has%20to%20make%20a%20long%20trip%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-much-should-you-tip-for-delivery-2023-7%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520drivers%2520Insider%2520interviewed%2520generally%2Cbill%2520%25E2%2580%2594%2520including%2520taxes%2520and%2520fees.%5C%22%3Ecustomers%20should%20take%20the%20distance%20they%20drove%20into%20consideration%20for%20their%20final%20tip%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20drivers%20and%20etiquette%20experts%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENavi%20Vong%2C%20a%20delivery%20driver%20who%20works%20for%20both%20DoorDash%20and%20Uber%20Eats%2C%20previously%20told%20Insider%20by%20email%20that%20%26quot%3Bwe%20select%20orders%20based%20on%20distance%20to%20the%20customer%20and%20how%20much%20the%20total%20offer%20is.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20added%20that%20%26quot%3Bcouriers%20use%20their%20own%20vehicles%2C%20complete%20with%20insurance%2C%20gas%2C%20and%20other%20maintenance%20costs%2C%26quot%3B%20so%20earning%20less%20than%20%2420%20and%20hour%20in%20the%20Phoenix%20area%20where%20she%20works%20%26quot%3Bis%20not%20enough%20for%20the%20cost%20it%20takes%20to%20maintain%20the%20vehicle%20to%20deliver%20in%20the%20first%20place.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EHotel%20staff%3A%20It%20varies%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20you're%20traveling%2C%20budget%20an%20extra%20%242%20to%20%245%20per%20night%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhousekeeper-hotel-san-francisco-shares-what-its-like-2023-8%5C%22%3Etip%20your%20housekeeper%20at%20a%20hotel%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Johnson%20said.%20Be%20sure%20to%20leave%20a%20tip%20daily%20as%20opposed%20to%20one%20lump%20sum%20at%20the%20end%2C%20as%20staffing%20may%20change%20day%20to%20day.%20The%20American%20Hotel%20%26amp%3B%20Lodging%20Association%20similarly%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ahla.com%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2FguestGratuityGuide.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecommends%3C%2Fa%3E%20leaving%20%241%20to%20%245%20per%20night%20for%20housekeeping.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20association%20also%20suggests%20tipping%20a%20valet%20or%20parking%20attendant%20%241%20to%20%245%20when%20your%20car%20is%20delivered%2C%20and%20any%20bell%20staff%20or%20porters%20%241%20to%20%245%20per%20bag%20they%20help%20you%20bring%20to%20your%20room.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20ask%20for%20an%20extra%20blanket%2C%20say%2C%20tip%20%242%20per%20item%20and%20%241%20for%20anything%20additional%20beyond%20that%2C%20according%20to%20the%20AHLA.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERoom%20service%20often%20comes%20with%20a%20service%20charge%20built%20in%2C%20but%20if%20it%20doesn't%2C%20aim%20for%2015%20to%2020%25%2C%20the%20association%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EBeauty%20services%3A%20Around%2020%25%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ETipping%20for%20beauty%20services%20at%20places%20like%20nail%20and%20hair%20salons%20should%20fall%20in%20the%20range%20of%2015%25%20to%2020%25%2C%20Johnson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELeighton%20agreed%2C%20adding%20that%20if%20there%20are%20multiple%20people%20that%20performed%20services%20for%20you%2C%20then%20you%20can%20ask%20for%20the%20tip%20to%20be%20divided%20among%20them.%3C%2Fp%3