3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Emperor%20Penguin%20chicks%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64e86555a7adf7001907ab06%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22980%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EEmperor%20Penguin%20chicks%20at%20colony%20Snow%20Hill%20Island%2C%20Antarctica%2C%20where%20part%20of%20the%20ice%20melted%20killing%20thousands%20of%20baby%20penguins.%3Cp%3EDavid%20Tipling%2FEducation%20Images%2FUniversal%20Images%20Group%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%20%3Cli%3EHuman-driven%20climate%20change%20is%20causing%20Antarctica%20to%20transform%20before%20our%20eyes.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3ECoastlines%20are%20crumbling%20from%20rapid%20permafrost%20melt%2C%20and%20snow's%20turning%20black%20from%20carbon%20pollution.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EAntarctica%20was%20once%20a%20pristine%20preserve%2C%20but%20humans%20are%20ruining%20it.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20ice%20beds%20holding%20thousands%20of%20Emperor%20penguins%20melted%20and%20broke%20apart%20from%20beneath%20their%20feet.%20Scientists%20estimated%20up%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F10000-baby-penguins-died-after-ice-bed-melted-broke-antarctic-2023-8%5C%22%3E10%2C000%20penguin%20chicks%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20too%20young%20to%20withstand%20the%20freezing%20waters%2C%20died%20as%20a%20result.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20just%20one%20of%20many%20disturbing%20changes%20that%20humans%20and%20human-driven%20climate%20change%20are%20causing%20to%20happen%20on%20the%20frozen%20continent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E1.%20Wildlife%20is%20disappearing%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAntarctica%20is%20home%20to%20more%20than%201%2C100%20species%20of%20plants%2C%20animals%2C%20and%20microbes%2C%20but%20probably%20not%20for%20long.%20Researchers%20estimate%20that%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.plos.org%2Fplosbiology%2Farticle%3Fid%3D10.1371%2Fjournal.pbio.3001921%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E65%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20all%20its%20wildlife%20could%20cease%20to%20exist%20by%20the%20year%202100.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAntarctica%20has%20been%20losing%20ice%20at%20an%20accelerating%20rate%20over%20the%20past%20few%20decades%2C%26quot%3B%20Emma%20MacKie%2C%20assistant%20professor%20in%20geological%20sciences%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Florida%2C%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225184%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Antarctica%20Ice%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F54f755166bb3f75e048a9c25%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223456%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMelting%20ice%20in%20Antarctica.%3Cp%3EAP%2FNatacha%20Pisarenko%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ERecent%20research%20found%20that%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fantarctica-most-intense-heat-wave-recorded-2023-9%5C%22%3Emost%20intense%20heat%20wave%3C%2Fa%3E%20ever%20recorded%20on%20Earth%20was%20in%20Antarctica%20last%20year.%20And%20this%20past%20winter%2C%20the%20frozen%20continent%20reached%20record-low%20sea%20ice%20levels.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEntire%20marine%20ecosystems%20are%20affected%20by%20such%20changes%20in%20sea%20ice%20cover%2C%26quot%3B%20Eric%20Rignot%2C%20a%20distinguished%20professor%20of%20Earth%20system%20science%20at%20the%20University%20of%20California%2C%20Irvine%2C%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat's%20more%2C%20%26quot%3Bwe%20have%20reason%20to%20believe%20that%20this%20ice%20loss%20trend%20will%20continue%20to%20worsen%2C%26quot%3B%20MacKie%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EData%20suggests%20that%20even%20if%20scientists%20try%20their%20best%20conservation%20strategies%2C%20they%20still%20won't%20be%20able%20to%20save%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.plos.org%2Fplosbiology%2Farticle%3Fid%3D10.1371%2Fjournal.pbio.3001921%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E37%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20life%20forms%20on%20the%20continent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E2.%20The%20ground%20is%20breaking%20apart%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fancient-viruses-may-reemerge-as-permafrost-melts-climate-change-study-2023-8%5C%22%3EPermafrost%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20soil%20or%20ground%20that's%20been%20frozen%20for%20at%20least%20two%20or%20more%20years.%20It's%20typically%20found%20in%20polar%20and%20hilly%20regions%20and%20is%20part%20of%20what%20holds%20Antarctica%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHuman-driven%20climate%20change%20is%20causing%20Antarctica's%20permafrost%20to%20thaw%20rapidly%2C%20according%20to%20NASA.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20permafrost%20thaws%20it%20can%20destabilize%20the%20ground%20and%2C%20in%20the%20case%20of%20shorelines%2C%20cause%20giant%20chunks%20of%20the%20continent%20to%20fall%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Permafrost%20thaw%20shows%20giant%20chunks%20of%20Earth%20falling%20into%20the%20ocean.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65120f5559fd710019f01568%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBeaufort%20Island%20is%20in%20Antarctica's%20Ross%20Sea.%20Permafrost%20melt%20is%20causing%20its%20shorelines%20to%20crumble.%3Cp%3EUSGS%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20region%20is%20nearing%20a%20threshold%20of%20rapid%20landscape%20change%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fglaciers.pdx.edu%2Ffountain%2FMyPapers%2FSudmanEtAl2017_PermafrostDecayDryValleysAntarctica.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresearchers%20noted%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202017.%20These%20changes%20are%20making%20the%20sea%20bed%20thinner%20and%20more%20mobile%2C%20they%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E3.%20Antarctica's%20pristine%20white%20snow%20is%20turning%20black%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAntarctica's%20once-white%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsnow-turns-back-siberia-russia-pollution-2019-