-quitting-hiring-act-your-wage-2023-5%3Fr%3DUS%26IR%3DT%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Equiet%20quitting%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20social%20media%2C%20and%20now%20some%20are%20discovering%20what%20it's%20like%20to%20be%20bored%20at%20work.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20hashtag%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2Ftag%2Fboredatwork%3Fis_from_webapp%3D1%26sender_device%3Dpc%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%23boredatwork%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20racked%20up%20over%20470%20million%20views%20on%20TikTok%20with%20young%20people%20sharing%20the%20realization%20that%20working%20life%20isn't%20what%20they%20expected.%20One%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2F%40anxiousanditshows%2Fvideo%2F7220908198948261166%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ETikToker%20posted%20a%20video%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20herself%20spinning%20around%20in%20her%20chair%20saying%3A%20%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20get%20your%20first%20corporate%20job%20and%20you're%20progressing%20at%20a%20faster%20pace%20than%20expected%20and%20constantly%20have%20nothing%20to%20do%20for%20half%20the%20day.%20I'm%20bored.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20TikToker%20who%20works%20at%20a%20hospital%20as%20a%20unit%20secretary%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2F%40cristinadxnisx_%2Fvideo%2F7113731053390466347%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%20shared%20a%20video%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20herself%20fidgeting%20at%20work%20in%20her%20uniform%20with%20text%20over%20the%20video%20saying%3A%20%26quot%3BDo%20I%20really%20get%20paid%20%2420%20an%20hour%20to%20sit%20and%20do%20nothing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20feeling%20may%20be%20new%20to%20Gen%20Z%20but%20being%20bored%20at%20work%20is%20an%20age-old%20phenomenon%20that%20workplace%20experts%20call%20%26quot%3Bboreout%26quot%3B%20and%20it%20can%20be%20just%20as%20harmful%20as%20burnout.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAndrew%20Brodsky%2C%20a%20management%20professor%20at%20The%20University%20of%20Texas%2C%20explained%20that%20boreout%20is%20when%20you're%20experiencing%20little%20%26quot%3Bstimulation%26quot%3B%20at%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBoreout%20is%20basically%20often%20the%20opposite%20extreme%20of%20burnout%2C%20but%20also%20can%20be%20just%20as%20problematic%20in%20terms%20of%20our%20work%20experience%2C%26quot%3B%20Brodsky%20said%20in%20an%20interview%20with%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20people%20don't%20often%20think%20about%20is%20that%20being%20under-stimulated%20can%20also%20create%20stress%20and%20negative%20feelings%20as%20well.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERuth%20Stock-Homburg%2C%20chair%20of%20the%20marketing%20and%20human%20resources%20department%20at%20Technische%20Universit%C3%A4t%20Darmstadt%20and%20an%20expert%20on%20boreout%2C%20explained%20that%20it%20is%20%26quot%3Ba%20largely%20neglected%20phenomenon%2C%26quot%3B%20at%20companies%20because%20workers%20may%20be%20ashamed%20to%20admit%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20contrast%20to%20boreout%2C%20burnout%20is%20something%20cool%2C%20because%20a%20person%20performs%20so%20much%2C%20which%20is%20so%20well%20appreciated%20in%20our%20society%2C%26quot%3B%20Stock-Humburg%20said%20to%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20usually%20hide%20their%20boreout.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoreout%2C%20when%20left%20untreated%2C%20can%20lead%20workers%20down%20the%20path%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquiet-quitting-great-resignation-trends-economy-outlook-leaving-jobs-davos-2023-1%3Fr%3DUS%26IR%3DT%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Equiet%20quitting%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20disengagement.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EBoreout%20originates%20from%20a%20lack%20of%20purpose%20at%20work%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20are%20looking%20for%20impactful%20roles%20more%20than%20ever%20now.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20particularly%20important%20to%20young%20workers%20between%20the%20ages%20of%2018%20to%2025%20who%20say%20%26quot%3Bmeaningful%20work%26quot%3B%20is%20one%20of%20the%20most%20motivating%20factors%20that%20keeps%20them%20in%20a%20job%2C%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjoinhandshake.com%2Fwp-content%2Fthemes%2Fhandshake%2Fdist%2Fassets%2Fdownloads%2Fnetwork-trends%2FGender-Equity-And-Gen-Z__Handshake-Network-Trends.pdf%3Fview%3Dtrue%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EHandshake%20report%20in%202022%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoreout%20starts%20to%20creep%20in%20when%20workers%20feel%20like%20their%20energy%20is%20being%20wasted%20on%20menial%20tasks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20often%20talk%20about%20extrinsic%20motivation%20which%20is%20related%20to%20pay%20and%20promotion%20but%20there's%20also%20intrinsic%20motivation%20which%20is%20whether%20we%20are%20interested%20in%20our%20own%20jobs%2C%26quot%3B%20Brodsky%20said%20adding%20that%20workers%20may%20not%20feel%20like%20they%20have%20enough%20variety%2C%20control%2C%20or%20autonomy%20over%20their%20own%20job.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStock-Humburg%20pointed%20out%20that%20boreout%20doesn't%20just%20affect%20%26quot%3Blosers%26quot%3B%20or%20those%20with%20low%20performance.%20Instead%20high%20performers%20could%20be%20prone%20because%20they%20can%20be%20impatient%20and%20desire%20exciting%20work.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJob%20crafting%20%E2%80%94%20also%20known%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquiet-thriving-empowering-career-strategy-joy-work-quiet-quitting-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Equiet%20thriving%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20is%20one%20way%20to%20overcome%20this%20feeling%20of%20boreout%20and%20it's%20%26quot%3Bthe%20idea%20that%20we%20can%20try%20and%20craft%20our%20own%20jobs%20to%20fit%20our%20motivations%20and%20what%20we're%20looking%20for%2C%26quot%3B%20Brodsky%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20could%20include%20mentoring%20other%20employees%2C%20finding%20ways%20to%20interact%20with%20people%20across%20your%20team%2C%20or%20even%20reframing%20the%20work%20in%20your%20own%20mind%20so%20that%20it's%20more%20exciting%20to%20you%20by%20asking%20yourself%20questions%20like%3A%20%26quot%3BHow%20can%20I%20make%20this%20work%20more%20fun%20in%20my%20own%20head%3F%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMonitoring%20employees%20leads%20to%20'busyness%20theater'%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20companies%20are%20keeping%20a%20closer%20eye%20on%20employees%20by%20using%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-bosses-use-employee-tracking-software-for-remote-workers-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Etechnology%20that%20monitors%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20how%20much%20they're%20working.%20Such%20tech%20can%20include%20tracking%20keystrokes%20per%20hour%20or%20monitoring%20how%20long%20they're%20actually%20clocked%20into%20work.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrodsky%20explained%20that%20boreout%20is%20often%20rooted%20in%20workplace%20cultures%20where%20employees%20are%20measured%20on%20how%20much%20they're%20working%20rather%20than%20the%20outcomes%20of%20their%20work.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%2043%25%20of%20employees%20in%20the%20US%20engage%20in%20so-called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-workers-use-productivity-theater-performative-work-to-look-busy-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%26quot%3Bproductivity%20theater%26quot%3B%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20more%20than%2010%20hours%20a%20week%20by%20doing%20things%20like%20attending%20too%20many%20meetings%20or%20sending%20lots%20of%20emails%20to%20appear%20busy%2C%20according%20to%20a%20Visier%20survey%20in%20May.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20busyness%20theatre%20can%20be%20a%20real%20source%20of%20boredom%20because%20someone's%20really%20just%20pretending%20to%20work%20and%20they're%20not%20actually%20using%20their%20mind%2C%26quot%3B%20Brodsky%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20it%20should%20be%20okay%20for%20employees%20to%20take%20a%20break%20and%20engage%20in%20stimulating%20activities%20from%20watching%20a%20video%20to%20relax%20or%20going%20for%20a%2015%20to%2020-minute%20jog%20so%20%26quot%3Byou%20can%20come%20back%20to%20work%20refreshed.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELotta%20Harju%2C%20an%20assistant%20professor%20of%20organizational%20behavior%20at%20EM%20Lyon%20Business%20School%20in%20France%2C%20added%3A%20%26quot%3BDon't%20assume%20that%20keeping%20people%20busy%20will%20cure%20boredom.%20It%20does%20not.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20explained%20it's%20a%20popular%20misconception%20that%20boreout%20comes%20from%20having%20inadequate%20work%20%E2%80%94%20workers%20can%20still%20get%20bored%20at%20companies%20where%20work%20piles%20up.%20Harju%20pointed%20to%20factors%20like%20red%20tape%2C%20organizational%20regulations%2C%20and%20role%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUltimately%20it's%20not%20just%20down%20to%20employees%20to%20make%20the%20work%20environment%20more%20stimulating%20for%20themselves.%20Managers%20also%20need%20to%20step%20up%20and%20have%20%26quot%3Bopen%20conversations%2C%26quot%3B%20with%20their%20direct%20reports%2C%20Brodsky%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BVery%20rarely%20are%20those%20in%20power%20asking%20those%20beneath%20them%20'What%20can%20I%20do%20to%20make%20your%20job%20better%3F'%20They%20can%20find%20ways%20to%20make%20the%20jobs%20objectively%20better%20so%20those%20employees%20perform%20better.%20Even%20just%20asking%20employees%20for%20their%20feedback%20makes%20them%20feel%20more%20involved%20in%20the%20workplace%2C%20makes%20it%20feel%20like%20their%20voice%20is%20more%20heard.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboreout-tiktok-workplace-phenomenon-opposite-burnout-still-harmful-workers-2023-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A16960644820