0about%2093%25%20of%20the%20Rs%202%2C000%20banknotes%20have%20returned%20to%20the%20banking%20system%20since%20the%20central%20bank%20in%20May%20decided%20to%20withdraw%20the%20high-value%20note%20from%20circulation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cbr%3E%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696060860000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.ndtvimg.com%2Fi%2F2016-11%2Frs-2000-notes-afp_650x400_61479281302.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Flast-date-to-exchange-rs-2-000-note-today-will-banknotes-be-valid-after-deadline-4437640%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22According%20to%20the%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20India%20(RBI)%2C%20from%20October%201%2C%20the%20Rs%202%2C000%20currency%20note%20will%20cease%20to%20have%20its%20value%20and%20will%20be%20just%20another%20piece%20of%20paper.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Flast-date-to-exchange-rs-2-000-note-today-will-banknotes-be-valid-after-deadline-4437640%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Flast-date-to-exchange-rs-2-000-note-today-will-banknotes-be-valid-after-deadline-4437640%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Flast-date-to-exchange-rs-2-000-note-today-will-banknotes-be-valid-after-deadline-4437640%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'End%20of%20Academic%20Autonomy'%3A%20Gujarat%20Public%20Universities%20Bill%20Draws%20Flak%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F30131641%2FThe-Wire-25.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3ECriticism%20against%20the%20recently%20passed%20Gujarat%20Public%20Universities%20Bill%20has%20been%20growing%2C%20with%20Opposition%20Congress%20accusing%20the%20state%20government%2C%20led%20by%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%2C%20of%20killing%20the%20autonomy%20of%20universities%20and%20transferring%20the%20powers%20to%20administer%20them%20to%20the%20state%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Gujarat%20Assembly%20passed%20the%20controversial%20Bill%20on%20September%2016%2C%20bringing%2011%20public%20universities%20in%20the%20state%20under%20the%20ambit%20of%20the%20said%20Bill%20and%20unifying%20different%20laws%20that%20governed%20the%20functioning%20of%20different%20universities.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20controversy%20stems%20from%20the%20sweeping%20changes%20the%20Bill%20wants%20to%20bring%20in.%20It%20intends%20to%20replace%20the%20existing%20senates%20and%20syndicates%20in%20the%20universities%20with%20a%20new%20system%20in%20place%20called%20the%20%E2%80%98board%20of%20management%E2%80%99%2C%20which%20will%20be%20given%20full%20executive%20control%20and%20be%20the%20final%20decision-making%20authority%20of%20a%20university%20to%20decide%20the%20policy%20course%20as%20well%20as%20to%20carry%20out%20all%20administrative%20work.%20This%20essentially%20means%20that%20there%20would%20not%20be%20any%20elections%20or%20any%20political%20activity%20by%20the%20student%20wings%20of%20any%20political%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fother-states%2Fgujarat-assembly-passes-the-common-university-bill%2Farticle67316058.ece%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20opposition%20Congress%20is%20of%20the%20view%20that%20the%20law%20would%20kill%20the%20autonomy%20of%20the%20public%20universities%2C%20for%20the%20stringent%20provisions%20in%20the%20Bill%20would%20infringe%20on%20the%20autonomy%20of%20the%20universities%20and%20are%20detrimental%20to%20academic%20freedom%20and%20internal%20functioning%20of%20the%20varsities.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20leader%20of%20the%20Congress%20legislature%20party%2C%20Amit%20Chavda%2C%20said%20that%20the%20Bill%20was%20aimed%20at%20%E2%80%9C%3Ci%3Esarkarikaran%20%3C%2Fi%3E(governmentisation)%20of%20education%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20newspaper%20reported.%20He%20also%20alleged%20that%20the%20Bill%20is%20actually%20meant%20to%20encourage%20privitisation%20of%20education%20in%20the%20state%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20undermining%20public%20universities.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Bill%20will%20end%20the%20academic%20and%20financial%20autonomy%20of%2011%20universities%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Congress%20particularly%20hit%20out%20at%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20decision%20to%20do%20away%20with%20the%20system%20of%20senates%20and%20syndicate%20bodies%2C%20which%20take%20up%20students%E2%80%99%20issues.%20They%20say%20it%20will%2C%20in%20effect%2C%20enable%20a%20culture%20where%20members%20close%20to%20the%20government%20or%20ruling%20party%20are%20appointed%20to%20administrative%20bodies%20in%20universities.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20state%20higher%20education%20minister%2C%20Rushikesh%20Patel%2C%20called%20the%20Bill%20a%20%E2%80%9Cmilestone%E2%80%9D.%20Arguing%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20government%2C%20he%20said%20the%20law%20would%20provide%20for%20%E2%80%9Csound%20finance%20control%2C%20better-quality%20higher%20education%20and%20measures%20to%20create%20excellent%20quality%20standards%20in%20the%20face%20of%20global%20competition%E2%80%9D.%20He%20said%20the%20law%20will%20equip%20the%20universities%20to%20cope%20with%20the%20requirements%20of%20the%2021st%20century.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAmong%20other%20highlights%20of%20the%20Bill%20is%20that%20it%20restricts%20the%20tenure%20of%20vice-chancellors%20to%20five%20years%20at%20a%20given%20university.%20If%20the%20person%20concerned%20is%20found%20%E2%80%9Ccompetent%E2%80%9D%2C%20s%2Fhe%20can%20be%20appointed%20in%20the%20same%20position%20at%20another%20university%20for%20another%20five%20years.%20The%20government%20reserves%20the%20right%20to%20remove%20a%20vice-chancellor%20from%20office%20if%20they%20are%20found%20to%20have%20an%20association%20with%20a%20political%20party%20or%20organisation.%20Again%2C%20it%20is%20for%20the%20government%20to%20decide%20whether%20a%20certain%20organisation%20is%20%E2%80%9Cpolitical%E2%80%9D%20in%20nature.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20state%20government%20will%20also%20wield%20powers%20to%20draw%20up%20eligibility%20criteria%20for%20members%20to%20be%20appointed%20to%20academic%20councils%2C%20exercised%20through%20the%20%E2%80%98board%20of%20management%E2%80%99%20it%20intends%20to%20set%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20new%20law%2C%20universities%20will%20have%20to%20enact%20%E2%80%9Cmodel%20statues%E2%80%9D%2C%20provided%20by%20the%20state%20government.%20Any%20changes%20to%20them%20will%20have%20to%20be%20made%20upon%20the%20approval%20of%20the%20government.%20The%20government%20would%20be%20fully%20empowered%20to%20draw%20up%20the%20same%2Funiform%20statutes%20for%20all%20universities.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20the%20Bill%20does%20not%20permit%20a%20university%20to%20debar%20a%20teaching%20or%20non-teaching%20staff%20member%20if%20s%2Fhe%20becomes%20a%20member%20of%20a%20legislative%20assembly%20or%20parliament%2C%20which%20has%20been%20the%20case%20thus%20far.%20Instead%2C%20the%20period%20they%20serve%20as%20legislators%20would%20be%20treated%20as%20a%20period%20of%20leave%20without%20pay.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696060725000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F30131641%2FThe-Wire-25.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Fend-of-academic-autonomy-gujarat-public-universities-bill-draws-flak%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20controversial%20Bill%20will%20do%20away%20with%20senates%20and%20syndicate%20bodies%2C%20and%20in%20its%20place%2C%20a%20new%20system%20of%20'board%20of%20management'%20will%20be%20created.%20No%20elections%20or%20political%20activity%20by%20the%20student%20wings%20of%20any%20political%20party%20will%20be%20allowed.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Fend-of-academic-autonomy-gujarat-public-universities-bill-draws-flak%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22As%20Maldives%20Goes%20to%20Polls%20in%20Final%20Run-Off%2C%20Cloud%20Over%20India's%20Development%20Projects%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F30132226%2FF7PuJImXEAAhyWN.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20As%20Maldivians%20flock%20to%20polling%20booths%20on%20Saturday%2C%20September%2030%2C%20the%20curtains%20draw%20on%20a%20presidential%20election%20that%20has%20seen%20a%20targeted%20opposition%20campaign%20which%20has%20put%20President%20Ibrahim%20Solih%20on%20the%20backfoot%20over%20his%20government%E2%80%99s%20relations%20with%20India.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBooths%20opened%20at%208%20am%20local%20time%20in%20Maldives.%20The%20outcome%20of%20the%20elections%20will%20be%20significant%20for%20India%20as%20the%20front-runner%20to%20be%20the%20next%20president%2C%20opposition%20candidate%20Mohamed%20Muizzu%20has%20led%20an%20electoral%20campaign%20based%20on%20bringing%20down%20Indian%20influence%20in%20the%20Indian%20ocean%20nation%2C%20which%20is%20coupled%20with%20his%20background%20of%20working%20closely%20on%20China%E2%80%99s%20Belt%20and%20Road%20projects.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20first%20round%2C%20the%20indelible%20ink%20was%20put%20on%20the%20index%20finger%20of%20the%20left%20hand%20of%20the%20voter.%20This%20time%2C%20the%20middle%20finger%20is%20being%20dabbed%20by%20the%20ink.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAround%2034%25%20of%20the%20Maldives%20electorate%20had%20voted%20by%2011%20am%20as%20per%20local%20reports.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20last%20election%20in%202018%2C%20the%20turnout%20had%20been%2089.22%25.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPolling%20booths%20will%20close%20at%205%20pm%20and%20counting%20is%20supposed%20to%20start%20around%20half%20an%20hour%20after%20the%20end%20of%20voting.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fmaldives-polls-solih-india-mohamed-muizzu-china%5C%22%3EMaldives%3A%20India%20Braces%20for%20Turbulence%20as%20China-Aligned%20Opposition%20Candidate%20Emerges%20Poll%20Favourite%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EThe%20setting%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20total%20number%20of%20eligible%20voters%20in%20Maldives%20is%20282%2C804%2C%20with%20women%20accounting%20for%20a%20higher%20percentage%20than%20men.%20This%20is%20the%20fourth%20presidential%20multi-party%20elections%20in%20the%20islands%20after%20the%20end%20of%20the%20dictatorship%20of%20President%20Maumoon%20Abdul%20Gayoom.%20It%20has%20the%20distinction%20of%20having%20the%20largest%20line-up%20of%20%E2%80%93%20eight%20%E2%80%93%20candidates%20on%20the%20ballot%20paper.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20first%20round%20of%20voting%20was%20held%20on%20September%209%2C%20but%20since%20none%20of%20the%20eight%20candidates%20won%20more%20than%2050%25%2C%20the%20top%20two%20had%20to%20go%20for%20a%20second%20and%20final%20run-off%20against%20each%20other.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETill%20now%2C%20no%20president%20has%20won%20a%20re-election%20in%20Maldives%20since%202008.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20most%20analysts%20had%20said%2C%20going%20into%20the%20first%20round%2C%20that%20the%20results%20would%20be%20too%20close%20to%20call.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20the%20results%20were%20rather%20clear%20cut.%20With%20a%2079%25%20turnout%20of%20voters%2C%20Muizzu%2C%20the%20candidate%20of%20the%20opposition%20Progressive%20Party%20of%20Maldives-People%E2%80%99s%20National%20Congress%20coalition%20obtained%2046%25%20of%20votes.%20Despite%20the%20ruling%20Maldivian%20Democratic%20Party%20(MDP)%20having%20the%20largest%20number%20of%20registered%20members%2C%20Solih%20came%20second%20with%2039%25%20of%20the%20votes.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F30132057%2FF7Mb5hNakAAtBBi.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F30132057%2FF7Mb5hNakAAtBBi.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F30132057%2FF7Mb5hNakAAtBBi-300x213.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F30132057%2FF7Mb5hNakAAtBBi-1024x728.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-677660%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22853%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EMDP%20supporters%20ahead%20of%20poll%20day%20in%20Maldives.%20Photo%3A%20X%2F%40eueommaldives23%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EPolitical%20equations%20after%20first%20round%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20the%20runner-up%20in%20the%20first%20round%2C%20incumbent%20President%20Solih%20has%20had%20an%20uphill%20task%20to%20get%20the%20right%20number%20of%20allies%20on%20his%20side%20to%20gain%20the%20numbers%2C%20at%20least%20on%20paper.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20third%20highest%20number%20of%20votes%20at%207%25%20were%20received%20by%20presidential%20candidate%20of%20the%20newly-formed%20The%20Democrats%2C%20Ilyas%20Labeeb.%20As%20the%20breakaway%20faction%20of%20the%20MDP%2C%20The%20Democrats%20were%20certainly%20more%20ideologically%20aligned%20to%20support%20Solih%2C%20rather%20than%20the%20PPM-PNC%20coalition.%20The%20MDP%20even%20agreed%20to%20hold%20a%20referendum%20on%20whether%20to%20change%20the%20governance%20from%20a%20presidential%20to%20a%20parliamentary%20system.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20the%20personal%20animosity%20between%20President%20Mohamed%20Nasheed%20and%20his%20childhood%20friend%20Solih%20runs%20deep.%20In%20the%20end%2C%20the%20Democrats%20decided%20not%20to%20officially%20endorse%20either%20Solih%20or%20Muizzu.%20However%2C%20Solih%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.sun.mv%2F84949%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eacknowledged%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20the%20splitting%20of%20MDP%20may%20cost%20the%20election.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Jumhoree%20Party%2C%20a%20former%20ruling%20alliance%20partner%2C%20had%20put%20its%20leader%2C%20business%20tycoon%20Qasim%20Ibrahim%20into%20the%20fray%2C%20but%20he%20came%20a%20disappointing%20fifth%20with%202.47%25%2C%20the%20lowest%20he%20has%20ever%20received%20in%20an%20election.%20But%20with%20his%20wealth%20and%20political%20experience%2C%20Qasim%20was%20ardently%20courted%20by%20the%20two%20main%20candidates%2C%20but%20he%20refused%20to%20endorse%20any%20one.%20However%2C%20his%20senior%20party%20members%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.sun.mv%2F84832%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eendorsed%20Solih%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndependent%20candidate%20and%20former%20home%20minister%20Umar%20Naseer%2C%20who%20came%20a%20surprising%20fourth%20in%20the%20polls%20with%203%25%20of%20the%20votes%2C%20had%20also%20decided%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Favas.mv%2Fen%2F135830%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Enot%20to%20endorse%20any%20candidate%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20However%2C%20his%20running%20mate%20Ahmed%20Saleem%20announced%20his%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.sun.mv%2F84972%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Esupport%20for%20Solih%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20a%20couple%20of%20days%20before%20voting%20day.%20Both%20the%20JP%20party%20members%20and%20Saleem%20gave%20former%20President%20Abdulla%20Yameen%E2%80%99s%20persecution%20of%20opposition%20leaders%20during%20his%20term%20as%20the%20reason%20for%20them%20supporting%20the%20MDP.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Miuzzi%20got%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fras.mv%2Fen%2Fpost%2F6312%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eearly%20support%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20from%20another%20presidential%20candidate%20Mohamed%20Nazim%E2%80%99s%20Maldives%20National%20Party.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESignificantly%2C%20a%20constituent%20of%20the%20three-party%20ruling%20coalition%20led%20by%20MDP%2C%20which%20had%20fielded%20Solih%20as%20candidate%2C%20broke%20away%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.sun.mv%2F84950%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eendorsed%20Muizzu%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20earlier%20this%20week.%20The%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.sun.mv%2F84928%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eargument%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20given%20by%20the%20MDA%E2%80%99s%20leader%20was%20that%20the%20MDP%20did%20not%20make%20adequate%20plans%20to%20gain%20ground%20after%20the%20shocking%20first%20round%20results.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2F671702%2Findia-ibrahim-solih-maldives-presidential-election%2F%5C%22%3EAhead%20of%20Maldives%20Presidential%20Polls%2C%20Solih%20Government%E2%80%99s%20Ties%20With%20India%20Emerge%20as%20Main%20Issue%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EA%20referendum%20on%20India%20relations%3F%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20India%2C%20this%20is%20an%20important%20election%20as%20New%20Delhi%20had%20invested%20heavily%20in%20development%20projects%20soon%20after%20Solih%20won%20the%20last%20polls%20in%202018.%20India%20had%20wanted%20to%20move%20quickly%20to%20gain%20ground%20that%20it%20had%20lost%20to%20China%20during%20President%20Yameen%E2%80%99s%20term%2C%20who%20had%20aligned%20himself%20to%20Beijing%20despite%20his%20declared%20%E2%80%98India%20First%E2%80%99%20policy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20opposition%20had%20focused%20relentlessly%20on%20Solih%E2%80%99s%20ties%20with%20India%2C%20especially%20on%20alleged%20stationing%20of%20Indian%20security%20personnel%20in%20Maldives.%20The%20Maldives%20government%20had%20dismissed%20that%20there%20was%20any%20Indian%20military%20activity%20on%20the%20island%20nation%2C%20but%20Solih%20admitted%20later%20after%20the%20first%20round%20defeat%20that%20the%20defence%20may%20not%20have%20been%20robust.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20day%20before%20voting%2C%20foreign%20minister%20Abdulla%20Shahid%20gave%20an%20interview%20to%20specifically%20address%20those%20concerns%2C%20stating%20that%20number%20of%20soldiers%20brought%20to%20operate%20the%20helicopter%20and%20dornier%20airplanes%20have%20not%20been%20changed%20since%20the%20Yameen%20government.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F18130803%2FUntitled-design-1-3.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F18130803%2FUntitled-design-1-3.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F18130803%2FUntitled-design-1-3-300x169.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F18130803%2FUntitled-design-1-3-1024x576.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-673479%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22675%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPrime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20meeting%20the%20President%20of%20Maldives%2C%20Ibrahim%20Mohamed%20Solih%2C%20in%20Male%2C%20Maldives%20on%20November%2017%2C%202018.%20Photo%3A%20PIB%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20previous%20Maldives%20government%20had%20attempted%20to%20not%20renew%20the%20visas%20of%20the%20Indian%20military%20personnel%20operating%20the%20aircraft%2C%20which%20had%20further%20nose-dived%20relations%20with%20New%20Delhi.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20fate%20of%20the%20major%20Indian%20development%20projects%20are%20also%20on%20balance.%20After%20Nasheed%20was%20overthrown%20in%20a%20coup%20in%202012%2C%20the%20new%20regime%20had%20unilaterally%20ended%20the%20contract%20of%20Indian%20conglomerate%20GMR%20group%20to%20operate%20and%20develop%20the%20Mal%C3%A9%20international%20airport.%20GMR%20had%20subsequently%20won%20the%20arbitration%20proceeding%20to%20get%20compensation%20from%20the%20Maldives%20government.%20Thereafter%2C%20major%20Chinese%20companies%20had%20come%20into%20Maldives%20and%20built%20major%20infrastructure%20projects%20in%20the%20island%20nation%2C%20strategically%20located%20on%20the%20major%20sea%20lanes%20of%20the%20Indian%20ocean.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETherefore%2C%20if%20Muizzi%20wins%2C%20the%20future%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20major%20development%20projects%2C%20most%20of%20them%20funded%20through%20Indian%20soft%20loans%20and%20grants%2C%20is%20uncertain.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696060417000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F30132226%2FF7PuJImXEAAhyWN.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fmaldives-election-solih-india-muizzu-voting-day%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20targeted%20opposition%20campaign%20has%20largely%20focused%20on%20President%20Ibrahim%20Solih's%20relations%20with%20India.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fmaldives-election-solih-india-muizzu-voting-day%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22As%20Maldives%20Goes%20to%20Polls%20in%20Final%20Run-Off%2C%20Cloud%20Over%20India's%20Development%20Projects%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F30132226%2FF7PuJImXEAAhyWN.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20As%20Maldivians%20flock%20to%20polling%20booths%20on%20Saturday%2C%20September%2030%2C%20the%20curtains%20draw%20on%20a%20presidential%20election%20that%20has%20seen%20a%20targeted%20opposition%20campaign%20which%20has%20put%20President%20Ibrahim%20Solih%20on%20the%20backfoot%20over%20his%20government%E2%80%99s%20relations%20with%20India.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBooths%20opened%20at%208%20am%20local%20time%20in%20Maldives.%20The%20outcome%20of%20the%20elections%20will%20be%20significant%20for%20India%20as%20the%20front-runner%20to%20be%20the%20next%20president%2C%20opposition%20candidate%20Mohamed%20Muizzu%20has%20led%20an%20electoral%20campaign%20based%20on%20bringing%20down%20Indian%20influence%20in%20the%20Indian%20ocean%20nation%2C%20which%20is%20coupled%20with%20his%20background%20of%20working%20closely%20on%20China%E2%80%99s%20Belt%20and%20Road%20projects.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20first%20round%2C%20the%20indelible%20ink%20was%20put%20on%20the%20index%20finger%20of%20the%20left%20hand%20of%20the%20voter.%20This%20time%2C%20the%20middle%20finger%20is%20being%20dabbed%20by%20the%20ink.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAround%2034%25%20of%20the%20Maldives%20electorate%20had%20voted%20by%2011%20am%20as%20per%20local%20reports.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20last%20election%20in%202018%2C%20the%20turnout%20had%20been%2089.22%25.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPolling%20booths%20will%20close%20at%205%20pm%20and%20counting%20is%20supposed%20to%20start%20around%20half%20an%20hour%20after%20the%20end%20of%20voting.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EThe%20setting%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20total%20number%20of%20eligible%20voters%20in%20Maldives%20is%20282%2C804%2C%20with%20women%20accounting%20for%20a%20higher%20percentage%20than%20men.%20This%20is%20the%20fourth%20presidential%20multi-party%20elections%20in%20the%20islands%20after%20the%20end%20of%20the%20dictatorship%20of%20President%20Maumoon%20Abdul%20Gayoom.%20It%20has%20the%20distinction%20of%20having%20the%20largest%20line-up%20of%20%E2%80%93%20eight%20%E2%80%93%20candidates%20on%20the%20ballot%20paper.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20first%20round%20of%20voting%20was%20held%20on%20September%209%2C%20but%20since%20none%20of%20the%20eight%20candidates%20won%20more%20than%2050%25%2C%20the%20top%20two%20had%20to%20go%20for%20a%20second%20and%20final%20run-off%20against%20each%20other.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETill%20now%2C%20no%20president%20has%20won%20a%20re-election%20in%20Maldives%20since%202008.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20most%20analysts%20had%20said%2C%20going%20into%20the%20first%20round%2C%20that%20the%20results%20would%20be%20too%20close%20to%20call.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20the%20results%20were%20rather%20clear%20cut.%20With%20a%2079%25%20turnout%20of%20voters%2C%20Muizzu%2C%20the%20candidate%20of%20the%20opposition%20Progressive%20Party%20of%20Maldives-People%E2%80%99s%20National%20Congress%20coalition%20obtained%2046%25%20of%20votes.%20Despite%20the%20ruling%20Maldivian%20Democratic%20Party%20(MDP)%20having%20the%20largest%20number%20of%20registered%20members%2C%20Solih%20came%20second%20with%2039%25%20of%20the%20votes.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F30132057%2FF7Mb5hNakAAtBBi.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F30132057%2FF7Mb5hNakAAtBBi.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F30132057%2FF7Mb5hNakAAtBBi-300x213.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F30132057%2FF7Mb5hNakAAtBBi-1024x728.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-677660%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22853%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EMDP%20supporters%20ahead%20of%20poll%20day%20in%20Maldives.%20Photo%3A%20X%2F%40eueommaldives23%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EPolitical%20equations%20after%20first%20round%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20the%20runner-up%20in%20the%20first%20round%2C%20incumbent%20President%20Solih%20has%20had%20an%20uphill%20task%20to%20get%20the%20right%20number%20of%20allies%20on%20his%20side%20to%20gain%20the%20numbers%2C%20at%20least%20on%20paper.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20third%20highest%20number%20of%20votes%20at%207%25%20were%20received%20by%20presidential%20candidate%20of%20the%20newly-formed%20The%20Democrats%2C%20Ilyas%20Labeeb.%20As%20the%20breakaway%20faction%20of%20the%20MDP%2C%20The%20Democrats%20were%20certainly%20more%20ideologically%20aligned%20to%20support%20Solih%2C%20rather%20than%20the%20PPM-PNC%20coalition.%20The%20MDP%20even%20agreed%20to%20hold%20a%20referendum%20on%20whether%20to%20change%20the%20governance%20from%20a%20presidential%20to%20a%20parliamentary%20system.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20the%20personal%20animosity%20between%20President%20Mohamed%20Nasheed%20and%20his%20childhood%20friend%20Solih%20runs%20deep.%20In%20the%20end%2C%20the%20Democrats%20decided%20not%20to%20officially%20endorse%20either%20Solih%20or%20Muizzu.%20However%2C%20Solih%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.sun.mv%2F84949%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eacknowledged%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20the%20splitting%20of%20MDP%20may%20cost%20the%20election.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Jumhoree%20Party%2C%20a%20former%20ruling%20alliance%20partner%2C%20had%20put%20its%20leader%2C%20business%20tycoon%20Qasim%20Ibrahim%20into%20the%20fray%2C%20but%20he%20came%20a%20disappointing%20fifth%20with%202.47%25%2C%20the%20lowest%20he%20has%20ever%20received%20in%20an%20election.%20But%20with%20his%20wealth%20and%20political%20experience%2C%20Qasim%20was%20ardently%20courted%20by%20the%20two%20main%20candidates%2C%20but%20he%20refused%20to%20endorse%20any%20one.%20However%2C%20his%20senior%20party%20members%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.sun.mv%2F84832%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eendorsed%20Solih%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndependent%20candidate%20and%20former%20home%20minister%20Umar%20Naseer%2C%20who%20came%20a%20surprising%20fourth%20in%20the%20polls%20with%203%25%20of%20the%20votes%2C%20had%20also%20decided%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Favas.mv%2Fen%2F135830%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Enot%20to%20endorse%20any%20candidate%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20However%2C%20his%20running%20mate%20Ahmed%20Saleem%20announced%20his%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.sun.mv%2F84972%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Esupport%20for%20Solih%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20a%20couple%20of%20days%20before%20voting%20day.%20Both%20the%20JP%20party%20members%20and%20Saleem%20gave%20former%20President%20Abdulla%20Yameen%E2%80%99s%20persecution%20of%20opposition%20leaders%20during%20his%20term%20as%20the%20reason%20for%20them%20supporting%20the%20MDP.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Miuzzi%20got%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fras.mv%2Fen%2Fpost%2F6312%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eearly%20support%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20from%20another%20presidential%20candidate%20Mohamed%20Nazim%E2%80%99s%20Maldives%20National%20Party.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESignificantly%2C%20a%20constituent%20of%20the%20three-party%20ruling%20coalition%20led%20by%20MDP%2C%20which%20had%20fielded%20Solih%20as%20candidate%2C%20broke%20away%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.sun.mv%2F84950%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eendorsed%20Muizzu%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20earlier%20this%20week.%20The%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.sun.mv%2F84928%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eargument%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20given%20by%20the%20MDA%E2%80%99s%20leader%20was%20that%20the%20MDP%20did%20not%20make%20adequate%20plans%20to%20gain%20ground%20after%20the%20shocking%20first%20round%20results.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EA%20referendum%20on%20India%20relations%3F%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20India%2C%20this%20is%20an%20important%20election%20as%20New%20Delhi%20had%20invested%20heavily%20in%20development%20projects%20soon%20after%20Solih%20won%20the%20last%20polls%20in%202018.%20India%20had%20wanted%20to%20move%20quickly%20to%20gain%20ground%20that%20it%20had%20lost%20to%20China%20during%20President%20Yameen%E2%80%99s%20term%2C%20who%20had%20aligned%20himself%20to%20Beijing%20despite%20his%20declared%20%E2%80%98India%20First%E2%80%99%20policy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20opposition%20had%20focused%20relentlessly%20on%20Solih%E2%80%99s%20ties%20with%20India%2C%20especially%20on%20alleged%20stationing%20of%20Indian%20security%20personnel%20in%20Maldives.%20The%20Maldives%20government%20had%20dismissed%20that%20there%20was%20any%20Indian%20military%20activity%20on%20the%20island%20nation%2C%20but%20Solih%20admitted%20later%20after%20the%20first%20round%20defeat%20that%20the%20defence%20may%20not%20have%20been%20robust.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20day%20before%20voting%2C%20foreign%20minister%20Abdulla%20Shahid%20gave%20an%20interview%20to%20specifically%20address%20those%20concerns%2C%20stating%20that%20number%20of%20soldiers%20brought%20to%20operate%20the%20helicopter%20and%20dornier%20airplanes%20have%20not%20been%20changed%20since%20the%20Yameen%20government.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F18130803%2FUntitled-design-1-3.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F18130803%2FUntitled-design-1-3.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F18130803%2FUntitled-design-1-3-300x169.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F18130803%2FUntitled-design-1-3-1024x576.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-673479%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22675%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPrime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20meeting%20the%20President%20of%20Maldives%2C%20Ibrahim%20Mohamed%20Solih%2C%20in%20Male%2C%20Maldives%20on%20November%2017%2C%202018.%20Photo%3A%20PIB%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20previous%20Maldives%20government%20had%20attempted%20to%20not%20renew%20the%20visas%20of%20the%20Indian%20military%20personnel%20operating%20the%20aircraft%2C%20which%20had%20further%20nose-dived%20relations%20with%20New%20Delhi.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20fate%20of%20the%20major%20Indian%20development%20projects%20are%20also%20on%20balance.%20After%20Nasheed%20was%20overthrown%20in%20a%20coup%20in%202012%2C%20the%20new%20regime%20had%20unilaterally%20ended%20the%20contract%20of%20Indian%20conglomerate%20GMR%20group%20to%20operate%20and%20develop%20the%20Mal%C3%A9%20international%20airport.%20GMR%20had%20subsequently%20won%20the%20arbitration%20proceeding%20to%20get%20compensation%20from%20the%20Maldives%20government.%20Thereafter%2C%20major%20Chinese%20companies%20had%20come%20into%20Maldives%20and%20built%20major%20infrastructure%20projects%20in%20th