logists-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMesolithic%20period%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20early%20Neolithic%20period%20when%20societies%20began%20to%20transition%20to%20agricultural%20ways%20of%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20team%20of%20researchers%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.eurekalert.org%2Fnews-releases%2F1003066%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUniversity%20of%20Alcal%C3%A1%20and%20the%20Autonomous%20University%20of%20Barcelona%3C%2Fa%3E%20analyzed%2076%20objects%2C%20including%20baskets%2C%20mallets%2C%20and%20sandals%2C%20that%20were%20discovered%20by%20miners%20two%20centuries%20ago%20while%20in%20the%20bat%20cave%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprehistoric-human-skull-cup-bone-tools-spain-cave-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECueva%20de%20los%20Murcielagos%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20press%20release%20from%20the%20Barcelona%20school%20stated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScientists%20previously%20found%20that%20bones%20discovered%20in%20the%20same%20cave%20may%20have%20been%20modified%20to%20be%20used%20as%20tools%20and%20drinking%20cups.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUsing%20carbon-14%20dating%2C%20which%20allows%20scientists%20to%20determine%20the%20age%20of%20an%20organic%20material%2C%20the%20Alcal%C3%A1%20and%20Barcelona%20researchers%20determined%20that%20the%2076%20objects%20were%20between%206%2C200%20and%209%2C500%20years%20old.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20there%20has%20been%20evidence%20of%20basketry%20dating%20back%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20years%2C%20basket%20weaving%20is%20often%20not%20tied%20with%20the%20hunter-gatherer%20societies%20of%20the%20Mesolithic%20era%20and%20is%20more%20associated%20with%20a%20sedentary%20lifestyle%20offered%20through%20an%20agrarian%20culture%20that%20dominated%20the%20Neolithic%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20quality%20and%20technological%20complexity%20of%20the%20basketry%20makes%20us%20question%20the%20simplistic%20assumptions%20we%20have%20about%20human%20communities%20prior%20to%20the%20arrival%20of%20agriculture%20in%20southern%20Europe%2C%26quot%3B%20Francisco%20Mart%C3%ADnez%20Sevilla%2C%20a%20researcher%20from%20the%20University%20of%20Alcal%C3%A1%20said%20in%20the%20press%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ENot%20exactly%20Nike%20Air%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20sandals%2C%20a%20pair%20of%20which%20had%20been%20on%20display%20at%20the%20National%20Archaeological%20Museum%20in%20Madrid%2C%20were%20made%20from%20crushed%20esparto%20grass%20which%20could%20have%20allowed%20the%20footwear%20to%20be%20flexible%2C%20according%20to%20the%20study.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20set%20of%20sandals%20is%20believed%20to%20have%20%26quot%3Ba%20small%20group%20of%20fibers%26quot%3B%20that%20may%20have%20been%20meant%20to%20go%20between%20the%20first%20and%20second%20toes%2C%20the%20study%20said%20%E2%80%94%20much%20like%20the%20strap%20found%20on%20flip-flops.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearchers%20also%20identified%20a%20%26quot%3Bbraid%20fixed%20to%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20sandal%26quot%3B%20that%20could%20have%20gone%20around%20the%20ankle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20sandal%20set%20therefore%20represents%20the%20earliest%20and%20widest-ranging%20assemblage%20of%20prehistoric%20footwear%2C%20both%20in%20the%20Iberian%20Peninsula%20and%20in%20Europe%2C%20unparalleled%20at%20other%20latitudes%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20study%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20the%20sandals%20showed%20signs%20of%20being%20worn%2C%20while%20others%20appeared%20unused%2C%20suggesting%20that%20some%20individuals%20had%20clothes%20prepared%20for%20them%20when%20they%20were%20buried%2C%20according%20to%20the%20study.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20esparto%20grass%20objects%20from%20Cueva%20de%20los%20Murci%C3%A9lagos%20are%20the%20oldest%20and%20best-preserved%20set%20of%20plant%20fiber%20materials%20in%20southern%20Europe%20so%20far%20known%2C%26quot%3B%20Mar%C3%ADa%20Herrero%20Otal%2C%20a%20researcher%20and%20co-author%20of%20the%20study%20said%20in%20the%20press%20release.%20%26quot%3BThe%20technological%20diversity%20and%20the%20treatment%20of%20the%20raw%20material%20documented%20demonstrates%20the%20ability%20of%20prehistoric%20communities%20to%20master%20this%20type%20of%20craftsmanship%2C%20at%20least%20since%209%2C500%20years%20ago%2C%20in%20the%20Mesolithic%20period.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20to%20whether%20the%20sandals%20were%20rocked%20with%20socks%20%E2%80%94%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsocks-and-sandals-fashion-dont-2016-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efashion%20offense%3C%2Fa%3E%20wouldn't%20appear%20until%20several%20millennia%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foldest-sandals-6200-years-neolithic-period-cueva-de-los-murcielagos-2023-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696045713000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65177ea85640b20019d78a82%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foldest-sandals-6200-years-neolithic-period-cueva-de-los-murcielagos-2023-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Researchers%20in%20Spain%20say%20they've%20found%20direct%20evidence%20of%20basketry%20in%20hunter-gatherer%20societies%20during%20the%20Mesolithic%20period%20in%20Europe.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22lloydlee%40insider.com%20(Lloyd%20Lee)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A12%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foldest-sandals-6200-years-neolithic-period-cueva-de-los-murcielagos-2023-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Duchess%20of%20York's%20former%20assistant%20murdered%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696045680000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F09%2F70x70%2Fskynews-duchess-of-york-jenean-chapman_6302903.jpg%3F20230930043937%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fduchess-of-york-shocked-and