re%20a%20firefight%20was%20happening.%20Four%20years%20earlier%2C%20in%20October%202018%2C%20the%20Saudis%20murdered%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-45812399%5C%22%3EJamal%20Khashoggi%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20who%20held%20a%20US%20green%20card%20and%20was%20a%20columnist%20for%20the%20%3Cem%3EWashington%20Post%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%93%20in%20Turkey%2C%20a%20NATO%20ally.%20Today%2C%20one%20of%20the%20most%20important%20foreign%20policy%20issues%20being%20pursued%20by%20the%20US%20administration%20is%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.al-monitor.com%2Foriginals%2F2023%2F09%2Fisrael-saudi-arabia-see-progress-ties-iran-sounds-warning%5C%22%3EIsrael-Saudi%20rapprochement%3C%2Fa%3E.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFor%20those%20wondering%20what%20will%20happen%20after%20Canada%E2%80%99s%20very%20public%20allegation%20of%20Indian%20involvement%20in%20the%20murder%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fhardeep-singh-nijjar-killing-khalistan-speculation%5C%22%3EHardeep%20Sing%20Nijjar%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20this%20is%20one%20possible%20pathway.%20Of%20course%2C%20Narendra%20Modi%20himself%20has%20a%20very%20personal%20experience%20on%20how%20to%20get%20away%20with%20murder.%20And%20the%20announcement%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fedition.cnn.com%2F2023%2F09%2F11%2Fmiddleeast%2Fus-india-gulf-europe-corridor-mime-intl%2Findex.html%5C%22%3Ethe%20trade%20route%3C%2Fa%3E%20connecting%20India%2C%20the%20UAE%2C%20Saudi%20Arabia%2C%20and%20Israel%20with%20Europe%20at%20the%20G20%20summit%20%E2%80%93%20after%20Canada%20would%20have%20shared%20intelligence%20with%20the%20US%20on%20the%20murder%20of%20Nijjar%20%E2%80%93%20is%20an%20important%20indicator%20of%20how%20the%20US%20and%20its%20allies%20will%20deal%20with%20things.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAdvocates%20of%20Henry%20Kissinger-style%20foreign%20policy%20would%20have%20it%20no%20other%20way.%20In%20their%20worldview%2C%20what%20matters%20is%20whether%20a%20state%20is%20an%20ally%20or%20an%20enemy.%20But%20an%20ally%20can%20also%20be%20more%20costly%20than%20they%20are%20worth%2C%20as%20Kissinger%20found%20out.%20Kissinger%2C%20as%20the%20Secretary%20of%20State%20under%20US%20President%20Richard%20Nixon%2C%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.npr.org%2F2023%2F09%2F10%2F1193755188%2Fchile-coup-50-years-pinochet-kissinger-human-rights-allende%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9Cthe%20dominant%20policymaker%20on%20Chile%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20involved%20destabilising%20the%20elected%20Chilean%20government%20under%20Salvador%20Allende%20and%20encouraging%20a%20military%20coup%20in%201973.%20Despite%20the%20atrocities%20that%20ensued%2C%20the%20US%20turned%20a%20blind%20eye.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20in%201976%2C%20Chilean%20agents%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdcist.com%2Fstory%2F16%2F09%2F21%2Fletelier%2F%5C%22%3Eassassinated%20a%20dissident%20in%20Washington%20DC%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20capital%20of%20the%20US%2C%20using%20a%20car%20bomb.%20This%20was%20the%20same%20year%20that%20Nixon%20resigned%20while%20facing%20impeachment%2C%20taking%20Kissinger%20with%20him.%20Due%20to%20the%20activities%20of%20the%20educated%20Chilean%20diaspora%20highlighting%20the%20atrocities%20under%20General%20Augusto%20Pinochet%20and%20Chilean%20acts%20of%20terrorism%20on%20US%20soil%2C%20there%20was%20a%20strong%20pushback%20by%20civil%20society%20and%20the%20US%20Congress%20against%20the%20US%20presidency%20and%20intelligence%20services.%20Jimmy%20Carter%2C%20who%20was%20elected%20in%201979%2C%20imposed%20sanctions%20against%20Chile%20in%201979.%20And%20even%20when%20Ronald%20Reagan%20%E2%80%93%20often%20seen%20as%20the%20ultimate%20US%20Cold%20War%20president%20%E2%80%93%20came%20to%20power%2C%20they%20stayed%2C%20even%20if%20Pinochet%20continued%20to%20rule%20until%201988%2C%20almost%20until%20the%20end%20of%20the%20Cold%20War.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20story%20of%20the%20US%20and%20Pinochet%20is%20particularly%20relevant%20as%20the%20US-China%20rivalry%20continues%20to%20heighten.%20India%20is%20a%20key%20player%20in%20this%20game%2C%20one%20that%20the%20US-led%20allies%20want%20on%20their%20side%2C%20so%20they%20will%20hold%20their%20noses%20and%20smile%20for%20the%20cameras.%20If%20Biden%20can%20go%20from%20calling%20Mohammad%20bin%20Salman%20%E2%80%93%20the%20crown%20prince%20of%20Saudi%20Arabia%20and%20allegedly%20key%20architect%20of%20Khashoggi%E2%80%99s%20murder%20%E2%80%93%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.commondreams.org%2Fnews%2F2022%2F07%2F15%2Fbone-saw-pariah-fist-bump-outrage-biden-greets-murderous-saudi-prince%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CMr%20Bone%20Saw%E2%80%9D%20to%20giving%20him%20a%20fist%20bump%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20surely%20the%20same%20applies%20to%20India%3F%20As%20it%20is%2C%20the%20US%20and%20its%20allies%20have%20a%20history%20of%20whitewashing%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20involvement%20in%20such%20crimes.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20there%20are%20important%20risks%20for%20the%20Biden%20administration%20in%20pursuing%20this%20line%20of%20action%20%E2%80%93%20possibly%20why%20the%20US%20administration%20has%20gone%20out%20of%20its%20way%20to%20say%20there%20are%20no%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fnijjar-killing-us-canada-no-special-exemption%5C%22%3Especial%20exemptions%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20countries%20to%20carry%20out%20targeted%20killings%20on%20foreign%20soil.%20The%20US%20will%20be%20aware%20that%20a%20closer%20engagement%20with%20leaders%20with%20terrible%20reputations%20%E2%80%93%20such%20as%20Saudi%20under%20Mohammad%20bin%20Salman%2C%20India%20under%20Modi%2C%20and%20Israel%20under%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%20%E2%80%93%20makes%20a%20mockery%20of%20the%20idea%20that%20the%20fight%20against%20China%20and%20its%20allies%20is%20about%20the%20%E2%80%98defence%20of%20democracy%E2%80%99.%20For%20China%2C%20Russia%2C%20and%20Iran%20%E2%80%93%20among%20others%20%E2%80%93%20the%20Canada-India%20diplomatic%20crisis%20is%20a%20windfall.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20also%20another%20issue%20in%20the%20Nijjar%20killing%20that%20makes%20it%20different%20from%20that%20of%20Abu%20Akleh%20and%20Khashoggi%20%E2%80%93%20it%20happened%20on%20the%20soil%20of%20a%20developed%20country.%20The%20US%20and%20its%20allies%20%E2%80%93%20Europe%2C%20Australia%2C%20Canada%20and%20New%20Zealand%2C%20will%20find%20this%20hard%20to%20swallow%20because%20it%20follows%20the%20China-Russia%20playbook.%20Both%20of%20these%20countries%20have%20regularly%20poured%20vitriol%20on%20the%20US%20and%20its%20allies%20for%20hosting%20people%20that%20China%20and%20Russia%20identify%20as%20%E2%80%9Csplittists%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cterrorists%E2%80%9D.%20Often%20these%20are%20vulnerable%20minorities%20who%20have%20faced%20persecution%2C%20such%20as%20Tibetans%2C%20Uyghurs%2C%20and%20Chechens.%20Sikhs%20who%20are%20non-violent%20proponents%20of%20the%20Khalistan%20cause%20%E2%80%93%20however%20India%20defines%20it%20%E2%80%93%20would%20fit%20perfectly%20into%20this%20set%20of%20people.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20576px)%2085vw%2C%20576px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F19140300%2FF6XA2MyWQAAYBoQ.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22576%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F19140300%2FF6XA2MyWQAAYBoQ.jpeg%20576w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F19140300%2FF6XA2MyWQAAYBoQ-300x225.jpeg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-673704%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22432%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EHardeep%20Singh%20Nijjar%E2%80%99s%20supporters.%20Photo%3A%20X%2F%40CitizenAnkit%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20Indian%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%2C%20instead%20of%20engaging%20w