ion%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F03%2F13090926%2F25372378539_a8d4c4de68_o.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20As%20many%20as%20113%20civil%20society%20organisations%20and%20776%20individuals%20from%20across%20the%20world%20have%20addressed%20a%20letter%20to%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20and%20health%20minister%20Manshukh%20Mandaviya%20seeking%20urgent%20intervention%20in%20the%20issue%20of%20shortage%20of%20drugs%20for%20TB%20patients.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20drug-resistant%20TB%20patients%20in%20India%20(such%20as%20TB%20patients%20on%20whom%20the%20first%20line%20of%20TB%20drugs%20don%E2%80%99t%20work%20and%20require%20advanced%20treatment)%20have%20been%20facing%20drug%20shortages%20for%20several%20months%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20recently%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhealth%2Fwill-the-un-high-level-meeting-address-indias-problem-of-tb-drugs-stock-out-situation%5C%22%3Epublished%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20piece%20capturing%20the%20voices%20of%20family%20members%20of%20TB%20patients%2C%20some%20civil%20society%20groups%2C%20state%20TB%20officers%2C%20and%20multilateral%20organisations%20like%20the%20WHO.%20Although%20these%20stakeholders%20expressed%20grave%20concern%20over%20the%20issue%2C%20the%20Indian%20government%20denied%20any%20such%20problem%20two%20days%20after%20the%20publication.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhealth%2Fwill-the-un-high-level-meeting-address-indias-problem-of-tb-drugs-stock-out-situation%5C%22%3EUnprecedented%20TB%20Drugs%20Stock-Out%20in%20India%3A%20Union%20Health%20Minister%20Skips%20UN%20High-Level%20Meet%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20health%20minister%20also%20skipped%20the%20UN%20high-level%20meeting%20on%20TB%20amidst%20this%20shortage.%20The%20meeting%20took%20place%20in%20New%20York%20on%20September%2022.%20Now%2C%20these%20TB%20advocacy%20groups%20have%20written%20the%20letter%20from%20New%20York.%20The%20groups%20and%20individuals%20come%20from%20Kenya%2C%20the%20United%20States%2C%20the%20United%20Kingdom%2C%20Zambia%2C%20Malawi%2C%20Uganda%2C%20Canada%2C%20Ghana%2C%20Cameroon%2C%20Indonesia%2C%20South%20Africa%2C%20India%2C%20and%20several%20other%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIndia%20has%20the%20highest%20TB%20burden%20in%20the%20world%2C%20and%20therefore%2C%20disease%20prevalence%2C%20or%20any%20hindrance%20in%20disease%20treatment%20in%20India%2C%20would%20be%20a%20key%20factor%20in%20the%20global%20elimination%20of%20TB.%20The%20WHO%20aims%20to%20eliminate%20TB%20globally%20by%202030%20while%20the%20Indian%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%20has%20set%20the%20target%20for%202025%20for%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20full%20letter%20and%20list%20of%20signatories%20is%20reproduced%20below%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETo%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHon.%20Prime%20Minster%20Narendra%20Modi%20152%2C%20South%20Block%2C%3Cbr%3E%20Raisina%20Hill%2C%3Cbr%3E%20New%20Delhi-110011%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHon.%20Mansukh%20Mandaviya%2C%3Cbr%3E%20Minister%20for%20Health%20and%20Family%20Welfare%20%26amp%3B%20Chair%20of%20the%20Stop%20TB%20Partnership%20Board%20Room%20No.%20348%2C%20%E2%80%98A%E2%80%99%20Wing%2C%3Cbr%3E%20Nirman%20Bhavan%2C%20New%20Delhi-110011%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20York%2C%20September%2022%2C%202023%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20People%20with%20TB%2C%20treatment%20providers%2C%20medical%20practitioners%2C%20survivor%20activists%2C%20civil%20society%20organizations%2C%20academics%2C%20writers%20and%20health%20journalists%20urge%20Indian%20Prime%20Minister%2C%20Narendra%20Modi%20and%20Health%20Minister%20Mansukh%20Mandaviya%20to%20take%20immediate%20steps%20to%20urgently%20address%20the%20issues%20of%20drug%20stock%20outs%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20TB%20programme.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EEven%20as%20the%20UN%20High%20Level%20Meeting%20on%20TB%20signed%20on%20a%20political%20declaration%20today%2C%20the%20country%20having%20the%20highest%20burden%20of%20TB%20and%20drug-resistant%20TB%20(DR-TB)%2C%20India%2C%20is%20now%20reporting%20chronic%20stockouts%20of%20anti-TB%20medicines.%20The%20frequent%20stockouts%20of%20anti-TB%20drugs%20threaten%20to%20undo%20gains%20made%20by%20India%E2%80%99s%20TB%20programme%20and%20also%20make%20the%20ambitious%20targets%20India%20has%20set%20for%20herself%20%E2%80%93%20to%20eliminate%20TB%20by%202025%2C%20five%20years%20before%20the%20SDG%20goal%20%E2%80%93%20unattainable.%20Uninterrupted%20supply%20of%20medicines%20is%20the%20first%20step%20to%20preventing%20drug%20resistance.%20The%20current%20stockouts%20are%20forcing%20people%20to%20go%20without%20treatment%20at%20catastrophic%20cost.%20Rajjab%2C%20a%20driver%20working%20with%20a%20private%20carpool%20company%20in%20Mumbai%20recently%20explained%20that%20%E2%80%9Cnow%2C%20neither%20the%20government%20is%20able%20to%20provide%20me%20with%20the%20medicines%2C%20nor%20are%20they%20available%20at%20the%20medical%20stores%E2%80%9D%20and%20he%20asks%20%E2%80%9Cif%20my%20wife%20dies%2C%20who%20would%20be%20held%20responsible%20for%20this%20crime%3F%E2%80%9D%20Those%20who%20can%20find%20and%20buy%20the%20drugs%20from%20the%20private%20sector%2C%20are%20feeling%20added%20out-of-pocket%20expenditure%20and%20the%20substantial%20financial%20burden%20on%20their%20families.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20facility%20level%2C%20the%20second%20line%20drug%20supply%20too%20has%20been%20erratic%20and%20there%20are%20reports%20that%20there%20is%20no%20supply%20of%20drugs%20for%20both%20multi%20drug%20and%20extensively%20drug%20resistant%20TB%20(XDR-TB)%20and%20states%20have%20been%20asked%20to%20procure%20the%20same%20locally.%20Drug%20stock%20outs%20at%20the%20state%20level%20may%20lead%20to%20further%20TB%20drug%20resistance%20in%20people%20who%20are%20forced%20to%20interrupt%20their%20treatment%2C%20which%20also%20means%20that%20their%20treatment%20may%20stop%20working%20for%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESince%20June%202023%2C%20there%20have%20been%20regular%20reports%20of%20stockouts%20of%20drugs%20used%20to%20treat%20TB%20and%20MDR-TB%20in%20several%20DOTS%20%26amp%3B%20DOTS-Plus%20Centres%20across%20the%20country.%20The%20persistent%20shortages%20have%20affected%20both%20first-%20and%20second-line%20TB%20drugs%2C%20including%20pediatric%20formulations.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20list%20of%20drugs%20that%20have%20been%20out%20of%20stock%2C%20since%20June%2C%20include%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMoxifloxacin%20(Lfx)%2C%20Cycloserine%20(Cs)%2C%20Linezolid%2C%20Clofazamine%2C%20Pyridoxine%2C%20Delamanid%20FGD-1st%20line%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFurthermore%2C%20India%20has%20lagged%20behind%20most%20other%20high%20burden%20countries%20in%20implementing%20the%20new%20BPaL%2FM%20treatment%20that%20is%20recommended%20by%20WHO%20as%20the%20preferred%20regimen%20for%20MDR-TB%20and%20shorter%20TB%20preventive%20therapy%20with%203HP.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20concerned%20group%20of%20TB%20activists%20from%20around%20the%20world%2C%20we%20call%20on%20the%20Government%20of%20India%20to%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Col%3E%20%3Cli%3EUndertake%20emergency%20procurement%20and%20reallocation%20of%20stocks%20to%20DOTS%20%26amp%3B%20DOTS%20Plus%20centers%20experiencing%20stockouts%20and%20shortages%20of%20anti-TB%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EExpedite%20drug%20procurement%2C%20improve%20inventory%20management%2C%20and%20strengthen%20supply%20chain%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EEnsure%20transparency%20and%20accountability%20in%20the%20supply%20chain%20management%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EUrgently%20roll%20out%20the%20shorter%2C%20simpler%2C%20more%20effective%2C%20new%20treatment%20BPaL%2FM.%20BPaL%2FM%20will%20not%20only%20improve%20patient%20outcomes%20but%20reduce%20risk%20of%20stockouts%20due%20to%20fewer%20medicines%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3ESufficiently%20allocate%20resources%20at%20the%20center%20and%20the%20state%20level%20to%20ensure%20a%20consiste